edge: Warren Zevon is the artist who sang the song 'Werewolves Of London'.
The band Sniff 'n' the Tears sang the song 'Driver's Seat'.
Rocky Burnette sang the song 'Tired of Toein' the Line'.

node_1: end of the world (party one more time)
edge: The PlaceMints sang a song called 'End of the World (Party One More Time)' which features Boogieman.
The group Cali Swag District sang the song 'Teach Me How to Dougie'.
April Wine sang the song 'Roller'.
Ada-Nicole Sanger covered the song 'U Can't Touch This' originally sung by MC Hammer.

node_1: dancing on top of the world (r8d!o's new swag remix)
edge: The PlaceMints sang a remixed version of 'Dancing on Top of the World' called 'R8d!o's New Swag Remix'.
The band Warrant sang the song 'Cherry Pie'.
Howard Jones sang a song called 'New Song'.
The band Haircut One Hundred sang the song 'Love Plus One'.
The Romantics sang the song 'One In a Million'.
The Outfield sang the song 'Say It Isn't So'.
Kevin James covered the song 'Bat Out of Hell' originally sung by Meat Loaf.
Generation X sang the song 'Dancing with Myself'. Billy Idol also covered this song.
Bryan Adams sang the song 'Heaven'.
The Stompers sang the song 'Never Tell an Angel'.
New Order sang the song 'Bizarre Love Triangle'.
The J. Geils Band sang the song 'Centerfold'.
The J. Geils Band also sang a song called 'Night Time'.
Van Halen did not sing any of the songs in this list, but they are mentioned here because their song 'Chance' is related to one of the other songs.
The song 'Chance' by Van Halen appears on their second album, titled 'Van Halen II'.
